#A generic term for a [[nephew]] or [[niece]].
#*'''1998''' Kin selection was strongest for choices between sibling and friend, decreasing across sibling vs. '''nibling''', '''nibling''' vs. friend, and '''nibling''' vs. cousin. &mdash; ''Relative worth across disparate types of assistance'', Kruger, D.J., May [http://www-personal.umich.edu/~kruger/ks-gen.html]
#*'''2004''' '''Nibling''' News &mdash; Rabbi Josh Yuter, Yutopia, January 29 [http://yutopia.yucs.org/archives/2004/01/nibling_news.html]
#*'''2005''' Cousins are informally referred to by the same terms used for siblings, but officially one has an aunt/uncle-'''nibling''' relationship with one's cousins. &mdash; ''The Body as a Cognitive Artifact in Kinship Representations'', N. J. Enfield, ''Current Anthropology'', Volume 46, Number 1, February
#*'''2005''' Next up: Probably Baby Norgi for my '''nibling''', though I also have socks and fingerless mitts that need starting. &mdash; "castiron" Casteel, ''The Bog of Lost Scholars'', December 7, [http://www.the-casteels.com/castiron/blog/index.php?topic=Crafts]

